## 4. SonarQube Quality Gate Models (LGPL-3.0)

The quality gate model layer in `crates/quality/src/gate/` is ported from
SonarQube Community Edition. This includes the following design patterns
and evaluation logic:

- `QualityGate` — Gate definition model (ported from `QualityGate.java`)
- `Condition` — Condition model with operator/threshold semantics (ported from `Condition.java`)
- `ConditionEvaluator` — Stateless condition evaluation engine (ported from `ConditionEvaluator.java`)
- `EvaluationResult` — Evaluation result with level and measure value (ported from `EvaluationResult.java`)
- `QualityGateStatus` — Aggregated gate status computation (ported from `QualityGateStatus.java`)

These ported components are subject to the **GNU Lesser General Public
License v3.0 (LGPL-3.0)**.

The quality gate configuration (`quality/quality-gate.yaml`), the built-in
rule engine (`crates/quality/src/rules/`), analysis providers
(`crates/quality/src/provider/`), and all integration logic are original
SoloDawn code licensed under Apache-2.0.

SonarQube is Copyright (C) SonarSource SA.

For the full LGPL-3.0 text, see: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html

